<!-- SEO ARTICLE — unique to EN -->
<section class="article-section">
<div class="ctr">
<div class="badge badge-dark">GUIDE</div>
<h2>Marketplace fulfillment in Ukraine: seller ratings, platform rules, and logistics strategy</h2>
<div class="article-content">
<h3>Understanding Ukrainian marketplace ecosystems</h3>
<p>Unlike Western markets dominated by Amazon, Ukraine has a diverse marketplace ecosystem with distinct audiences and rules. Rozetka functions as a full-service marketplace with buyer protection and standardized seller accounts. Prom.ua operates more like an aggregator with 100 million product listings and seller-customizable storefronts. Kasta focuses on fashion and lifestyle with daily flash sales. OLX dominates classifieds with 60 million monthly visits. Each platform has its own commission structure, listing requirements, and fulfillment expectations &mdash; understanding these differences is critical for international sellers.</p>

<h3>Why seller ratings determine your marketplace success</h3>
<p>On Rozetka and Prom.ua, seller ratings are heavily weighted toward shipping speed and order accuracy. A seller who ships within 24 hours and maintains less than 2% return rate receives algorithmic preference in search results and promotional placements. A single day of missed shipments can drop your rating for weeks and bury your listings below local competitors. This is precisely why marketplace sellers need a fulfillment partner with same-day dispatch guarantees and redundant infrastructure &mdash; your logistics directly determines your visibility and revenue.</p>

<h3>Multi-platform inventory strategy</h3>
<p>The most successful international sellers on Ukrainian marketplaces list on 3-5 platforms simultaneously. The key challenge is inventory synchronization: if a product sells on Rozetka, the stock level must update on Prom.ua, Kasta, and OLX instantly to prevent overselling. MTP Group's WMS maintains a single inventory pool with real-time sync across all connected platforms. When an order arrives from any marketplace via API, the system reserves stock, generates a picking task, and updates all other channels within seconds.</p>

<h3>Product listing localization: more than translation</h3>
<p>Ukrainian marketplace buyers expect product descriptions in Ukrainian. But effective localization goes beyond Google Translate. Top-performing listings on Rozetka include benefit-focused titles (not just product names), detailed specifications in a standardized format, lifestyle photos alongside studio shots, and SEO-optimized descriptions that rank in marketplace search. We connect international sellers with Ukrainian content specialists who understand platform-specific formatting requirements and search algorithms.</p>

<h3>Marketplace commissions and payment flows</h3>
<p>Commission rates vary significantly: Rozetka charges 5-20% depending on category, Prom.ua charges a monthly subscription plus per-listing fees, and Kasta operates on a consignment model for fashion brands. Payment settlement cycles also differ &mdash; typically 7-14 days after delivery confirmation. Understanding these economics is essential for pricing your products competitively while maintaining margins. At MTP Group's fulfillment rates (from $0.41/order), your total cost per sale on most platforms remains well below what you would spend using a Western European 3PL.</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>

